# CODEOWNERS
#
# Each line assigns ownership of a file pattern to a team or individual.
# The LAST matching rule wins.
#
# Syntax: <pattern>   @<owner>
# Owners can be: @org/team-slug  or  @github-username
#
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ── Default owner for everything ─────────────────────────────────────────────
*                           @YOUR_ORG/YOUR_TEAM_NAME

# ── CI / repo configuration requires team lead review ────────────────────────
.github/                    @YOUR_ORG/YOUR_TEAM_NAME
Dockerfile*                 @YOUR_ORG/YOUR_TEAM_NAME
docker-compose*.yml         @YOUR_ORG/YOUR_TEAM_NAME

# ── Docs can be reviewed by anyone on the team ───────────────────────────────
docs/                       @YOUR_ORG/YOUR_TEAM_NAME

# ── Example: assign a sub-path to a specific person ──────────────────────────
# src/auth/                 @specific-github-username
